--- body ---
## Context

`skills/harness-rules/coding.md` is auto-invoked for every project via the
harness-rules skill. It opens with `## Python (3.10+)` and encodes uv sync,
pytest mark conventions, and subprocess patterns. LaTeX, R, and Go projects
receive these rules even though they are irrelevant.

The file is not wrong for Python projects — the rules are sound. But loading
it unconditionally adds noise and risks confusing the agent on non-Python work.

## Actions

Option A (light): Add a frontmatter scope note: "Apply only when the project
has a pyproject.toml or requirements.txt." The agent skips irrelevant sections.

Option B (split): Extract Python rules to `coding-python.md` alongside a
`coding-latex.md`, `coding-r.md`. The SKILL.md auto-invokes only the files
relevant to the current project's detected stack.

Option A is cheaper; Option B is more principled. Decide at implementation time.

## Exit criteria

- Non-Python projects do not receive Python-specific coding rules.
- Python projects still receive them.
- No regression on existing Python project workflows.
